            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1225301407,
            "creation_date": 1225301407,
            "body": "<p>For distributed Event processing you could use <a href=\"http://esper.codehaus.org/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Esper<\/a>.It could process up to 500 000 event/s on a dual CPU 2GHz Intel based hardware.It's very stable because many banks use this solution. It supports JMS input and output adapter based on Spring JMS templates. So you could use any JMS implementation for event processing, i.e. <a href=\"http://activemq.apache.org\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">ActiveMQ<\/a>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 247693,
            "question_id": 181225
        },
        {
            "owner": {
